Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNN) for visual recognition tasks such as image classification, object detection, and scene labeling. This suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel latent CNN framework, which involves treating the most discriminate region as a latent variable, and jointly learning the global CNN with the latent CNN. This suggests that the paper also belongs to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of benchmark datasets such as CIFAR-10, CIFAR100, MNIST, and PASCAL VOC 2007 Classification dataset, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
